
[Richmond, 5 Mch. 1781. Minute in War Office Journal (Vi) under this date: A letter to the Governor, respecting the 200 Cartouch boxes he required me to collect, informing that the States Cartouch boxes at Petersburg had been sent to Chesterfield Courthouse by order of Baron Steuben, before Capn. Brownes messenger got there, and asking if an Order shall be issued for 50 boxes from Col. Goodes that are lodged in his care. Another minute, same day: Answer from the Governor to the letter respecting cartouch boxes. He directs that those wanted shall be sent for to Col. Goodes. Directed the Commissary of Military Stores accordingly. Muters letter and TJs reply have not been located.]
